Elorza for Mayor Campaign Office Grand Opening
Dustin Moskovitz was invited
Celebrate with us in our beautiful new office in the historic Stanley Building! Thanks to your hard work, our movement and our team are growing every day – and now we've finally got an office to match it. If you don't yet know Jorge Elorza, this is your chance to meet him and the whole campaign team, and learn more about his vision for One Providence. Light refreshments will be provided, and we'll have campaign schwag on hand. Please join us for a night of celebration and continue to support our goal of electing Jorge Elorza as our next Mayor of Providence! This event is FREE and OPEN TO THE PUBLIC. This is NOT a fundraising event.
Friday, May 23, 2014, 6 PM - 8 PM in EDT
190 Broad Street 3rd Floor East

BangOn!NYC presents New Year's Eve 2014: TIME & SPACE
Dustin Moskovitz was invited
***REMEMBER TO BRING A PRINTED COPY OF YOUR TICKET*** This New Year's Eve, BangOn!NYC will be taking over a full-block warehouse in East Williamsburg, featuring: Space Stage: Deniz Koyu https://soundcloud.com/denizkoyu The Polish Ambassador http://thepolishambassador.com/ Space Jesus https://www.facebook.com/spacejesusmusic Time Stage: Damian Lazarus http://damianlazarus.com/ Behrouz https://soundcloud.com/djbehrouzmusicdownload Sleepy & Boo http://www.residentadvisor.net/dj/sleepyboo Special Live performance by Bob Moses! https://soundcloud.com/the-bob-moses CLICK HERE FOR SET TIMES AND LOCATION!!!! http://www.brownpapertickets.com/event/fb/496002 This year’s theme “Time & Space" will be set inside a 60,000 sq ft multi-room arena with 2 main stages of electronic music, custom lighting, and stage design. Featuring illuminated art installations, circus performers flying overhead, Burning Man Art Cars (including Thunder Gumbo), themed lounge areas, food trucks, funky clothing vendors, onsite body painting by Kirkworx Dupuis and Bodyworx.me (www.facebook.com/bodyworxdotme) plus much much more Our midnight countdown will feature a rocket launch and aerial performance you won’t want to miss... Also featuring: Team Kitty Koalition Wildlight (Polish Ambassador Side Project) https://soundcloud.com/wildlight Cumba Mela http://www.cumbamela.com/ Devon James https://soundcloud.com/devon-james Gino Santos https://soundcloud.com/gino-santos Rambo Springsteen http://facebook.com/djrambospringsteen The Magick Report https://soundcloud.com/the-magick-report Kellam https://www.soundcloud.com/kellam The Golden Pony https://soundcloud.com/thegoldenpony Sean Glass https://soundcloud.com/seanglass Pete Fraser (Disco Knights) Special Host Kayvon Zand +Full Lineup TBA 699 Scholes St, at the corner of Onderonk Ave, Brooklyn, 11237. December 31st, 2013 9pm-6am Get Tickets Here http://www.brownpapertickets.com/event/fb/496002 VIP Table reservations available and highly encouraged, please email kelly@bangon-nyc.com for more info. We have a massive door and coat check team ready to expedite your entry. We recommend early arrival as there is generally a large rush from 10:30-12:30. Brought to you by BangOn!NYC With Pabst Blue Ribbon, our official NYE beer partner Special thanks to: Red Bull Zico Perky Jerky
Tuesday, December 31, 2013 at 9:00pm - Wednesday, January 1, 2014 at 6:00am in EST
699 Scholes St, at the corner of Onderonk Ave, Brooklyn, 11237.

Climate Theater, 37 North, anonEvents & Get YER Freak on! present: 3rd Annual SUPERHERO Street Fair Saturday September 22, 2012 2pm to Midnight Where ordinary people do extraordinary things! Come as the SuperHero you are with you own superpower! Location: The boardwalk oasis overlooking beautiful Islais Creek, newly renovated for 2012 Entrance: Indiana @ Cesar Chavez (one block West of 3rd on Cesar Chavez) Live and electronic music on 5 stages Local Heroes awards ceremony SuperHero climbing wall Intergalactic vendors Vapor Room green space Super food and beverages OM Shan-tea ceremony house Supperclub super relaxation beds and lounge Bring out the SuperHero in you. As every year, a portion of the proceeds from this festival go to the recipients of the awards. Please check out the winners under the "Awards" of the SuperHero website. CATHEDRALS Release Second Single "Harlem"!
Dustin Moskovitz was invited
Hey guys! We’re thrilled to announce that we've released our 2nd single “Harlem” this morning which Neon Gold calls “a breathless, quixotic dream.” Thanks to your support, our first single "Unbound" hit #1 on Hype Machine and has since garnered over 300k plays on Soundcloud and over 300k Youtube views! We could never have done it without you. We'd love your help in getting back to the top of the charts with this release so if you dig it please favorite and share our latest jam! We promise more to come soon :) Heart and Share here: http://hypem.com/track/22q98/C+A+T+H+E+D+R+A+L+S+-+Harlem Love, CATHEDRALS ‡ p.s. big thanks to all the friends that helped make this track awesome, especially Max Savage behind the console and Sean Hutchinson on drums. big shoutout to Turntable Kitchen for putting this on limited vinyl in December and Neon Gold Records for the love and support! <3
